  "local_port": 58666,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My WhatsApp web is not working. I'm using the Chrome browser on my Windows 8.1 laptop, and the internet speed is decently good. I opened web.whatsapp.com and the QR code doesn't load up at all. It just keeps going round and round. How can I fix this?",
  "response": "If WhatsApp Web isn't loading the QR code on your Chrome browser, here are some troubleshooting steps you can try:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Clear Cache and Cookies**\n   - Open Chrome, click the three dots (Menu) > **Settings** > **Privacy and Security** > **Clear Browsing Data**.\n   - Select **Cookies and other site data** and **Cached images and files**.\n   - Click **Clear Data**, then reload the WhatsApp Web page.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Disable Extensions**\n   - Some Chrome extensions (like ad blockers or VPNs) may interfere with WhatsApp Web.\n   - Go to **chrome://extensions** and disable extensions one by one to see if the issue is resolved.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Check Your Internet Connection**\n   - Ensure your internet connection is stable. Try loading other websites to confirm.\n   - If you're on a restricted network (e.g., office or school Wi-Fi), WhatsApp Web may be blocked.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Update Chrome**\n   - Open Chrome, click the three dots (Menu) > **Help** > **About Google Chrome**.\n   - If an update is available, install it and restart the browser.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Use Incognito Mode**\n   - Open Chrome in Incognito Mode (Ctrl + Shift + N) and try accessing WhatsApp Web.\n   - This disables extensions and uses a clean session, which can help identify the issue.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Check Date and Time Settings**\n   - Incorrect date and time settings can cause issues with websites.\n   - Make sure your system's date and time are correct.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Restart Your Computer**\n   - Sometimes, a simple restart can resolve temporary glitches.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Try Another Browser**\n   - Use an alternative browser like Firefox or Microsoft Edge to access WhatsApp Web.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Check WhatsApp's Server Status**\n   - Visit [Downdetector](https://downdetector.com/) or WhatsApp\u2019s official Twitter account to see if there\u2019s a service outage.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Reinstall Chrome**\n   - If none of the above steps work, uninstall Chrome, restart your laptop, and reinstall the latest version.\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Check for Software Conflicts**\n   - Some antivirus or firewall software may block WhatsApp Web. Temporarily disable them and check if the issue persists.\n\n---\n\nIf the problem persists after trying these steps, consider reaching out to WhatsApp support for further assistance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
